The paper discusses the vulnerability of machine learning models to membership inference attacks, which is a security and privacy concern in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses information theory to measure the amount of information leakage and investigates properties of machine learning models and training algorithms, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
